==The Four Aspects of the Contemporary Property Crisis==

"There are at least four structural crises at the core of property and ownership that
underscore the inadequacies of existing paradigms and necessitate a profound
transformation of managing the world through this singular lens.


* OBJECTIFICATION

Objectification of land, nature,
labor, and information,
obscuring interdependence


* EXTRACTION

Detachment of property rights
from embodied responsibilities
of stewardship leading to
systemic negative externalities


* CENTRALIZATION

Optimization of abstract,
exclusive rights leading to
growing concentration of
ownership of the means of
production and benefits derived
from them


* CONTROL

Top-down regulatory practices
failing to manage complex and
contextual systems of value
creation and extraction, and their
externalities and impacts."

- [[Property and Beyond Lab]] [https://cdn.sanity.io/files/gg6r1tfm/production/f3f1f5ded2fb8b9f94ed2b847cfcdec76f3fbc8d.pdf pdf]

